net.bytebuddy.instrumentation.type

Interface TypeDescription

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AnnotatedElement, ByteCodeElement, DeclaredInType, ModifierReviewable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    InstrumentedType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InlineInstrumentedType, InstrumentedType.AbstractBase, SubclassInstrumentedType, TypeDescription.AbstractTypeDescription, TypeDescription.ForLoadedType

    public interface TypeDescription
extends ByteCodeElement, DeclaredInType, ModifierReviewable, AnnotatedElement
    Implementations of this interface represent a Java type, i.e. a class or interface.

      • getActualModifiers

        int getActualModifiers(boolean superFlag)

        Returns the type's actual modifiers as present in the class file. For example, a type cannot be private. but it modifiers might reflect this property nevertheless if a class was defined as a private inner class.

        Unfortunately, the modifier for marking a static class collides with the SUPER modifier such that these flags are indistinguishable. Therefore, the flag must be specified manually.

        Parameters:
        superFlag - true if the super flag should be set.
        Returns:
        The type's actual modifiers.
